<promed@promedmail.org>

[A pause of 3 or 4 days between HPAI outbreaks without a new focus discovered on farms does not seem to justify implying "dormancy."

The extremely severe control measures contemplated by South Korea's animal and public health authorities could be explained by the unusual, unfortunate combination of 3 factors that they are facing:
1. HPAI H5N8 in wild birds (seemingly, large scale);
2. HPAI H5N8 outbreaks on duck and now also chicken farms;
3. The timing of the Lunar New Year festivities, characterised by increased consumption/sales/slaughter of poultry and mass population movements (travels).

It is hoped that infections by the circulating virus strains remain restricted to avians.

A political map of South Korea is available at http://www.vidiani.com/?p=4303. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1BIE, http://healthmap.org/r/1BIE, http://healthmap.org/r/1BIE.]
